# Copy to frontend/.env for LOCAL dev. In deployment, these are set as Netlify
# build environment variables on each SITE: the dev site (koslist-dev → dev.koslist.au)
# uses the dev project values; the prod site (koslistau → koslist.au) uses prod values.
#
# All VITE_* vars are PUBLIC (Vite inlines them into the client bundle by design).
# netlify.toml's SECRETS_SCAN_OMIT_PATHS keeps the secrets scanner from flagging them.
#
# dev and prod are SEPARATE Supabase projects (not branches):
#   dev  = tabletree-dev  (ogxjrvhrwoltkcncprcf)
#   prod = tabletree      (ifyvsrmdnmqlqifcqpnx)
#
# | var                          | dev (tabletree-dev)      | prod (tabletree)         |
# |------------------------------|--------------------------|--------------------------|
# | VITE_SUPABASE_URL            | dev project API URL      | prod project API URL     |
# | VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY       | dev project anon key     | prod project anon key    |
# | VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY  | pk_test_… (sandbox)      | pk_live_… (live)         |
#
# Stripe SECRET keys are NOT here — they live as the STRIPE_SECRET_KEY secret on
# each Supabase project (sk_test_ on dev, sk_live_ on prod). See README > Environments.

# Defaults below point at the dev project "tabletree-dev" (ref ogxjrvhrwoltkcncprcf) —
# the correct target for local dev. For prod "tabletree" (ref ifyvsrmdnmqlqifcqpnx), use:
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://ifyvsrmdnmqlqifcqpnx.supabase.co
#   VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_FXVsKctcVMYQYzTczzxcug_8brkCsGi
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://ogxjrvhrwoltkcncprcf.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_nrYaSY3dYN6VaROsFCPuxg_ohiX2h6-

# Stripe publishable key. Use a sandbox pk_test_ key for local/dev.
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_stripe_sandbox_publishable_key
